background-color: white; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; margin-bottom: 6px;\">I love getting e-mail, and thank you all for sending it to me, but I only have the opportunity to check that on p-day (which is Thursdays for now). While I\'m in the MTC there is a service that will print letters and deliver them. With the subject line of \"Elder Andrew Finlayson\" you can send letters to letter@mtcmexicocarepackage.com.  For now I just steal Elder Andersen\'s letters from his family, he thinks it is funny.  I have bonded with Elder Andersen we are best friends!</p>\r\n<p style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-top: 6px;\">My first week was hard. My companion, Elder Jones is from Idaho, and our roommates are from Mexico. I am able to have small conversations and was able to co<span style=\"display: inline;\">mmit an \"investigator\" to baptism. Mission prep was so wonderful, but there is so much that I want to teach, but don\'t know how to say it in Spanish. I suppose that will come.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-top: 6px;\">We have 4 missionaries in our district from the US that will be going to Culiacan together.  I love being with the other missionaries.  I have made wonderful friends already, and excited to be able to go into the mission field with them.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; display: inline; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 6px;\">Please continue to pray for me as I study Spanish, that I will be able to pick up the language quickly. Please pray that I will have patience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; margin-top: 6px;\">Love you all\r\nElder Finlayson</p>\r\n\r\n</div>','\"There is lots and lots of Spanish here!\"','','publish','open','open','','there-is-lots-and-lots-of-spanish-here','','','2015-11-11 17:32:42','2015-11-11 17:32:42','',0,'',0,'post','',1),(10,2,'2015-10-17 00:03:00','2015-10-17 00:03:00','<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/mexico-mtc-sign-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"266\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align: left;\">Elder Finlayson entered the Mexico CCM on Wednesday, October 14, 2015.  What a wonderfully emotional day for all of us! He will be in Mexico City until November 23 and would love to hear from friends and family.  His address is here on the blog along with an email address.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align: left;\">We don\'t know much but that he arrived, said that he was safe and asked for us to write letters.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align: left;\">We are grateful that he is willing to serve the Lord and the people of Mexico.  Your prayers on his behalf in learning the language would be great.  There is great power in prayer.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align: left;\">His Prep Day will be on Thursday while in the CCM so we will send updates as we get them.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0013.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0013-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"263\" border=\"0\" /></a></div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0018.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0018-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"131\" border=\"0\" /></a></div>\r\n<a style=\"clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0014.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0014-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"131\" border=\"0\" /></a>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\">Elder Finlayson with Nana &amp; Papa</div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a style=\"clear: center; float: center; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0021.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0021-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"320\" height=\"212\" border=\"0\" /></a></div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\">Good bye hugs with the siblings (Allen is honorary brother)</div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: left;\"><a style=\"clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0045.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0045-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"133\" border=\"0\" /></a><a style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0047.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0047-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"133\" border=\"0\" /></a><a style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0046.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_004