nd none of our investigators came to church which was even sadder. It is very hard knowing how the gospel can change their lives, but they don\'t want to listen.  On a good note, we have been working with the old branch president, he hasn\'t been to church in like 3 years and he did come to church so that was good.\r\n\r\nI am learning quickly that Satan has a firm grip on people here.  One of our investigators has decided to check into drug rehab and when we went to see another one, we found out that her mom had checked her into a drug rehab because she is using and selling drugs.  There are lots of drugs here.\r\n\r\nI have lost my English scriptures, so for personal study I have been reading Jesus the Christ which is good, and doing lots of Spanish study.  The highlight of my week is that we bought a small tree and it has lights.\r\n\r\nIn the book of John we receive the account of Christ saying feed my sheep and earlier Christ tells them to wait for him in Galilee.  So obedient as they were they went to Galilee and waited and waited they just sat there. Then Peter being the senior apostle said I am going to fish because that is what Peter knew. When the Lord asked Peter if he loved him 3 times and all three times with the same answer. Then only a few days later he had denied Christ,then Christ said something like (not scripture but what i get from it ) then Peter, why are you here? Why are we having this same talk we had a few years ago? Why did you go back to your nets? Do you love the fish more than me? From this experience Peter became the miracle worker he was. Christ has gives us a similar charge, wait for the second coming watch for the signs and when he comes again (by my study not to far off btw) he will say to those passively waiting,  what are you doing? do you not love me? Yes Peter was in Galilee but the Lord needed him to proclaim the words of Christ. Needed him to be a witness that He is our redeemer and that He lives. He took up the grave and He payed for all of our sins.  When Christ comes I want Him to see me and say thank you, you knew my will, wait for me but teach others of me, and feed My sheep.\r\n\r\nMy day starts at 5AM, when we get up and go to the gym. We workout, shower and eat breakfast until 8. Personal study until 9, companion study until 10, and then language study until 11. Then we start out for the day, and try to make appointments for the afternoon (most of the people don\'t have phones, so it\'s knocking on doors to make appointments) or teach some lessons. We do this until 2, when we go to a members home for lunch (generally soup). Back out to teach from 3 until 8. We have to be back to our apartment by 8 or 8:30. We\'ll make some dinner and then clean up and go to bed.','Week 8 - Not much to report','','publish','open','open','','week-8-not-much-to-report','','','2015-12-14 18:29:27','2015-12-14 18:29:27','',0,'http://www.elderfinlayson.com/?p=98',0,'post','',0),(100,2,'2015-12-14 17:53:06','2015-12-14 17:53:06','(This week Elder Finlayson did not have much to say, I will try to piece together what he sent us)\n\nWe are working very hard teaching this week.  We are still working with the Primary President, you know what they say, Up hill both ways!  We seem to always be going up hill in the world and with our spirits.\n\nOur days are mostly the same, I almost get hit by a bus, we try to contact lots of people, we walk up the mountain for most of the day and then I try to ride down the mountain which is a bad idea, every time I almost die because the roads are not paved. The area is super different...we did see a cock fight on our way to a lesson the other day so that was cool.\n\nWe had an investigator say that he does not want to take the lessons anymore.  This made me cry, and none of our investigators came to church which was even sadder.  On a good note, we have been working with the old branch president, he hasn\'t been to church in like 3 years and he did come to church so that wa