img class=\"alignnone wp-image-137\" src=\"http://www.elderfinlayson.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/pn_another_pd.jpg\" alt=\"pn_another_pd\" width=\"395\" height=\"296\" /></a>\r\nHere is a recap of our week:\r\n\r\nThis Tuesday was good we tried for a lot of work but didn\'t get much which is the story for this week but that\'s okay the Lord blesses us for trying right?\r\n\r\nTuesday: knock 22 doors 5 answer 1 let us in\r\n\r\nWednesday: just a lot of the same stuff we knocked 34 doors and 15 answered and 3 let is in It was good really, just very very different missionary work here.\r\n\r\nThursday: day before new years no one let us in. we knocked 33 doors and not one let us in tried to contact 10 people they all were like no\r\n\r\nFriday: its the 31st, we cleaned our house and had 5 appointments, sure 3 of them dropped and weren\'t there but we still are trying right :)\r\n\r\nSaturday: today was really good we had a lot of work 7 lessons that\'s a record for one day it was crazy for real\r\n\r\nSunday: we meet a drunk guy today it was really funny. the only words people know in English are cuss words and they love to use them lol. So we got cussed out 2 times but we had 54 people at sacrament meeting and<strong> 1 investigator came</strong> !!!!!!!!!! we are bouncing off the walls someone came to church!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.elderfinlayson.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/pn_christmas_call.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-138\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-138\" src=\"http://www.elderfinlayson.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/pn_christmas_call.jpg\" alt=\"pn_christmas_call\" width=\"239\" height=\"179\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIts in the book of <a href=\"https://www.lds.org/search?q=Matthew+24%3a9-11&amp;lang=eng&amp;domains=scriptures\">Mathew chapter 24 versus 9-11</a> we learn about the apostasy and the need for an apostasy in the world. the apostasy is a time when the priesthood authority, the authority to act in the name of God isn\'t on the earth, and because of the apostasy there was a need for a restoration a coming or renewing of the church that Christ had established on the earth. One thing that is important to know is the difference between a restorer and a reformer. A reformer, as pg 36 in preach my gospel tells us, is someone who changes what is there into something else, but to restore is to bring something back to its original form. <a href=\"https://www.lds.org/search?domains=scriptures&amp;lang=eng&amp;query=D%26C+45%3A28\" target=\"_blank\">D&amp;C 45:28</a> invites us to come forth and take a part of the restoration. Part of the restoration was restoring of the priesthood keys, the authority to act in Gods name here on earth. We read in Malachi that there will be a restoration and that Elijah the prophet will come and will restore the keys of the kingdom. We read the account of this happening in <a href=\"https://www.lds.org/search?domains=scriptures&amp;lang=eng&amp;query=D%26C+110%3A13+-+16+\" target=\"_blank\">D&amp;C 110:13 - 16 </a> after all of this we also read in <a href=\"https://www.lds.org/search?domains=scriptures&amp;lang=eng&amp;query=Matthew+18%3A16\" target=\"_blank\">Matthew 18:16</a> that the truth will be born by the mouth of 2 witness and the Book of Mormon is another witness, another testimony of Jesus Christ and so the true church must have the Book of Mormon or it could not be true. I know that this church is true I know it with all my heart and I love it and that is why I am here on my mission. I know Joseph was a true prophet and he restored the truth back to the earth and me along with many many other men have that authority to act in the name of God.','Week 12,','','publish','open','open','','week-12','','','2016-01-10 05:24:09','2016-01-10 05:24:09','',0,'http://www.elderfinlayson.com/?p=134',0,'post','',0),(135,1,'2016-01-06 12:32:17','2016-01-06 12:32:17','','pn_christmas_tree_lights','','inherit','open','closed','','pn_christmas_tree_lights','','','2016-01-06 12:32:17','2016-0