 33 doors and not one let us in tried to contact 10 people they all were like no\r\n\r\nFriday: its the 31st, we cleaned our house and had 5 appointments, sure 3 of them dropped and weren\'t there but we still are trying right :)\r\n\r\nSaturday: today was really good we had a lot of work 7 lessons that\'s a record for one day it was crazy for real\r\n\r\nSunday: we meet a drunk guy today it was really funny. the only words people know in English are cuss words and they love to use them lol. So we got cussed out 2 times but we had 54 people at sacrament meeting and<strong> 1 investigator came</strong> !!!!!!!!!! we are bouncing off the walls someone came to church!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.elderfinlayson.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/pn_christmas_call.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-138\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-138\" src=\"http://www.elderfinlayson.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/pn_christmas_call.jpg\" alt=\"pn_christmas_call\" width=\"239\" height=\"179\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIts in the book of <a href=\"https://www.lds.org/search?q=Matthew+24%3a9-11&amp;lang=eng&amp;domains=scriptures\">Mathew chapter 24 versus 9-11</a> we learn about the apostasy and the need for an apostasy in the world. the apostasy is a time when the priesthood authority, the authority to act in the name of God isn\'t on the earth, and because of the apostasy there was a need for a restoration a coming or renewing of the church that Christ had established on the earth. One thing that is important to know is the difference between a restorer and a reformer. A reformer, as pg 36 in preach my gospel tells us, is someone who changes what is there into something else, but to restore is to bring something back to its original form. <a href=\"https://www.lds.org/search?domains=scriptures&amp;lang=eng&amp;query=D%26C+45%3A28\" target=\"_blank\">D&amp;C 45:28</a> invites us to come forth and take a part of the restoration. Part of the restoration was restoring of the priesthood keys, the authority to act in Gods name here on earth. We read in Malachi that there will be a restoration and that Elijah the prophet will come and will restore the keys of the kingdom. We read the account of this happening in <a href=\"https://www.lds.org/search?domains=scriptures&amp;lang=eng&amp;query=D%26C+110%3A13+-+16+\" target=\"_blank\">D&amp;C 110:13 - 16 </a> after all of this we also read in <a href=\"https://www.lds.org/search?domains=scriptures&amp;lang=eng&amp;query=Matthew+18%3A16\" target=\"_blank\">Matthew 18:16</a> that the truth will be born by the mouth of 2 witness and the Book of Mormon is another witness, another testimony of Jesus Christ and so the true church must have the Book of Mormon or it could not be true. I know that this church is true I know it with all my heart and I love it and that is why I am here on my mission. I know Joseph was a true prophet and he restored the truth back to the earth and me along with many many other men have that authority to act in the name of God.','Week 12,','','inherit','closed','closed','','134-revision-v1','','','2016-01-10 05:24:09','2016-01-10 05:24:09','',134,'http://www.elderfinlayson.com/?p=144',0,'revision','',0),(145,2,'2016-01-12 22:52:10','2016-01-12 22:52:10','Martes (Tuesday)\r\n\r\nToday was district meeting it was a good meeting verdad la nuevo misssionarios in la districtas premer junta sorry i wrote in Spanish it is a little tough lol.  After the district meeting we had zone meeting it was good we set goals for the transfer we have a goal of 12 baptisms as a zone 30 lessons a week as a companionship and 25 contacts a week as a companionship so we have a lot of work to do lol 25 contacts is my favorite part I don’t even need my comp to do that now I can contact!!! i get a little tripped up some times and then my comp helps :) so we only had a half day to work because district meting but we had 6 contacts\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nmiercoles\r\n\r\nbien dia hoy (good day today) me and my Comp got to do some service this morning it was really cool we got to cut grass with machetes.  It was hard but new and I liked it I felt like I was Ammon but instead of cutting arms I was cutting grass it was so dope lol bien ciddo verdad. during the day we contacted and worked with some member’s lots of work that’s like all we do but we love the work este die es la dia de ray we ate a special cake bread stuff it was really good it had little baby dolls in it, it was little weird\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\njeves\r\n\r\ngood day today only 4 contacts I am a little sad about that but we tried talking to a lot of people today. so we went and visited a less active Guadalupe and we brought the branch president with us he was a big help in that lesson please keep her in y’alls prayers she has 8 kids 1 works in Culiacan he is 18 she has a daughter who had a kid at 13 and then at 14 ran away and they haven’t hurd from her in 2 years and now she is having problems with her marriage its just a really hard time for her we are working so hard with her she still has 6 more kids and they are such a good familia\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nviernes\r\n\r\ngood day today for real we have weekly planning on viernes planned for 9 people that this week we will be focusing most of our time on we are ready for the week not really lol we just barely got our money :( we were dyeing lol we had no food) so fun story for the day today we tried to contact a guy and he told us he was a crystal meth addict and if we didn’t leave him alone he would shank us lol we were like ok bye lol it was a little freaky but we just kept going and doing our thing talking to as many people will listen\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDomingo\r\n\r\nwe had another investigator come to church this week but the problem is he lives in the rehab center and so we have limited visiting hours it’s so tuff but we are keeping smiles on our face and keep working :) so another difference between here and the stated in the states when someone is mad at you or doesn’t want to listen to you in the states they slam the door here you have to sit there as they cuss you out and yell at you in a verbal assault and there is nothing you can do about it you have to just take it by the end of the day you want to hate them but you just can’t your heart won’t let you','Week 13 A mix of English and Spanish','','publish','open','open','','week-13-a-mix-of-english-and-spanish','','','2016-01-12 22:52:10','2016-01-12 22:52:10','',0,'http://www.elderfinlayson.com/?p=145',0,'post','',0),(146,2,'2016-01-12 00:16:08','2016-01-12 00:16:08','Martes (Tuesday)\r\n\r\ntoday was district meeting it was a good meeting verdad la nuevo misssionarios in la districtas premer junta sorry i wrote in Spanish it is a little tough lol after the district meeting we had zone meeting it was good we set goals for the transfer we have a goal of 12 baptisms as a zone 30 lessons a week as a companionship and 25 contacts a week as a companionship so we have a lot of work to do lol 25 contacts is my favorite part I don’t even need my comp to do that now I can contact!!! i get a little tripped up some times and then my comp helps :) so we only had a half day to work because district meting but we had 6 contacts\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nmiercoles\r\n\r\nbien dia hoy (good day today) me and my Comp got to do some service this morning it was really cool we got to cut grass with machetes.  It was hard but new and I liked it I felt like I was Ammon but instead of cutting arms I was cutting grass it was so dope lol bien ciddo verdad. during the day we contacted and worked with some member’s lots of work that’s like all we do but we love the work este die es la dia de ray we ate a special cake bread stuff it was really good it had little baby dolls in it, it was little weird\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\njeves\r\n\r\ngood day today only 4 contacts I am a little sad about that but we tried talking to a lot of people today. so we went and visited a less active Guadalupe and we brought the branch pres